<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,600,1743]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1573,1599]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from the Latin word 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leschen &amp; Reid &amp; Nadein" authorityYear="2020" box="[946,1007,1574,1599]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Maurodus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arcus">
<emphasis box="[946,1007,1574,1599]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">arcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
one meaning of which is “rainbow”, referring to the 
<typeStatus box="[326,374,1609,1635]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">type</typeStatus>
locality of this new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
